  "title": "Process Engineer [5 days, Oil & gas, Tuas]",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Working Hours & Salary</strong></h2><ul><li><p><strong>Working Days:</strong> 5 days per week</p></li><li><p><strong>Salary:</strong> SGD 3,500 – SGD 4,000 </p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Train staff on new processes and develop operating instructions and manuals</p></li><li><p>Analyze production schedules, processes, and technical specifications</p></li><li><p>Prepare material and equipment lists, purchase orders, cost analyses, and production cost estimates</p></li><li><p>Design and optimize production processes to improve efficiency and reduce waste</p></li><li><p>Maintain process documentation and prepare production and performance reports</p></li><li><p>Establish design and production standards in collaboration with management and end users</p></li><li><p>Plan facility layouts and determine manpower requirements</p></li><li><p>Develop and implement process improvements and technology upgrades</p></li><li><p>Design control systems to minimize production issues and operational costs</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Nitec/Higher Nitec/Diploma in Industrial Engineering or related field</li><li>Able to interpret engineering drawing</li><li>Knowledge of precision machining, production scheduling and production management</li><li>Proven similar working experience in precision machining industry</li></ul><p>﻿Aurora AsiaPacific (21C0671) | Stephanie Luan (R21100585)</p>",
